HEADWORD: Scout
<hw>Scout</hw> <pr>(skout)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Icel.
<ets>sk⟦umac⟧ta</ets> a small craft or cutter.]</ety> <def>A swift
sailing boat.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So we took a <qex>scout</qex>, very much pleased with the manner
and conversation of the passengers.</q> <rj><qau>Pepys.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

